  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "A ***euphemism*** is a mild or indirect expression substituted for one considered too harsh, blunt, or direct. \"Passed away\" for \"died,\" \"let go\" for \"fired,\" \"collateral damage\" for \"civilian deaths.\" Euphemism softens — which is sometimes kind and sometimes dishonest, depending on what's being softened and why.",
